%YAML 1.1
%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 1cb8db85de55fa142bafb539466ab76c, type: 3}
  m_Name: TutorialDatabase
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  entries:
  - triggerKey: game_start
    message: Welcome to <i>Incinder!</i>\nYou are a Seeker, sent alone into the depths
      of this cathedral to retrieve an ancient blood goblet. Traverse its crumbling
      rooms. Loot chests for helpful items. Face the creatures that lurk within...
      Use the shadows to your advantage, harness blood magic to overcome those who
      stand in your way and find the goblet. Do that, and your mission is complete.\n<b>Left-click</b>
      anywhere to move.
  - triggerKey: first_move
    message: You're on the move!\nMove freely out of combat, but in combat only a
      set amount. Want to investigate the room without moving? Use <b>WASD</b> to
      move the camera, and hold <b>right-click</b> to pivot it.
  - triggerKey: first_ability_selected
    message: Abilities are your main tools in combat. Press <b>1</b>, <b>2</b>, or
      <b>3</b>, or <b>click</b> the buttons at the bottom to select one, then click
      a target/area to cast it. Hover over the ability buttons to learn their details.
      To cancel, press the same key again.
  - triggerKey: first_attack
    message: Good job, you got them!\nBefore confirming a target, you can press <b>Space</b>
      to <i>gamble</i> a coin flip. Success increases damage by 50%, but failure
      halves it. You can see enemy health by hovering over them, or at the top of
      the screen in combat.
  - triggerKey: first_spotted
    message: You've been spotted!\nThe enemy is on their way. Try staying in the
      shadows to slip past, or strike first before they see you.
  - triggerKey: first_combat
    message: Combat has begun!\nThe coins are your Action Points - spend them to
      use your abilities. You can see how far you can move each turn based on the
      line from you to your mouse.
  - triggerKey: first_damage_taken
    message: You took a hit!\nKeep an eye on your health in the bottom left. If it
      reaches zero, your quest is over - that's a complete reset back to the very
      beginning.
  - triggerKey: first_chest_open
    message: You found some items!\nSelect one of 3 options to take with you. Afterwards,
      press <b>Tab</b> or click the bag icon to open your inventory and click items
      to equip or unequip them. You can only have 5 items equipped at a time.
  - triggerKey: first_combat_win
    message: Victory!\nKeep exploring - somewhere in these ruins lies a powerful
      artifact. If things get too dangerous, try sneaking through the shadows to
      slip past enemies undetected. Good luck on your quest!
